[{"content":"<p><br /> Are you the type of person that is more likely to give help to a colleague in need? Or are you more likely to take all you can get from everyone you work with?<br /></p>","type":"text/html"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<p><br /> Wharton professor Adam Grant explores in his book “Give and Take” whether being a giver or a taker makes you more successful in the business world.<br /></p>"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<p><br /> Grant found that selfless givers may earn about 14% less than takers, but that ultimately they are in a better position to go farther in their careers and they last longer when they make it to the top.<br /></p>"},{"content":"<p><br /> Take the quiz below to find out whether you are a giver or a taker.<br /></p>","type":"text/html"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<div class="pd-embed" id="pd_1396896993"></div>"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<script type="text/javascript">
